stylometry: Decision trees are important in solving problems because they give you information and results that can be graphed out in a sequence in which you can see and are able to follow throughout the whole process.  They allow a person to see the decisions people make and the probabilities they will make those certain decisions based on other groups of data given in the model.  An example of a decision tree than can be used can be the probability a person will go to eat fast food or just make themselves food at home.  The model would give us information such as a good economy or bad economy but in this example we could use a person has a lot of time to spare, little time to spare, or whether or not the person is in a good mood or bad mood.  Both of these issues can be used in the decision of whether or not to go eat fast food.  We would then develop the decision tree based on the results given in the problem and the percentage of whether or not the person is in a good mood, or if they have little time to spare.
